# Deployment Topology Rules

## Intent
Define deployment boundaries for Railway, Vercel, and GitHub Releases in the rewrite.

## Environment Topology
- Deploy core API/services to Railway.
- Canonical user-facing runtime is Railway unless explicitly re-decided.
- Vercel is allowed for UI preview/design iteration workflows.
- Release Android artifacts via GitHub Releases from CI.

## Configuration Rules
- Keep environment variables separated by environment and platform.
- Use GitHub Actions environments with approval gates for production deploys.
- Keep deploy configuration declarative and versioned in repo.

## v0 Usage Rules
- v0-assisted UI changes are allowed only for web presentation layers.
- v0/Vercel flows are for design iteration and code generation, then merged into repo.
- All v0-generated code must pass the same lint/type/test/compliance gates.
- v0-generated code cannot bypass shared contracts, policy middleware, or compliance requirements.

## Prohibited
- Manual production deploys outside approved CI workflow paths.
- Cross-environment secret reuse between staging and production.